      "id": "https://boingboing.net/2026/03/13/when-you-stop-eating-may-matter-more-than-what-you-eat-for-better-sleep.html",
      "url": "https://boingboing.net/2026/03/13/when-you-stop-eating-may-matter-more-than-what-you-eat-for-better-sleep.html",
      "title": "[Boing Boing] When you stop eating may matter more than what you eat for better sleep",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/night-eating.jpg?fit=1200%2C800&quality=60&ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/13/when-you-stop-eating-may-matter-more-than-what-you-eat-for-better-sleep.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"When you stop eating may matter more than what you eat for better sleep\"><img alt=\"fast-stock/shutterstock.com\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/night-eating.jpg?fit=1200%2C800&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1200\" /></a><p>A three-hour buffer between your last meal and bedtime improved circadian rhythms, blood pressure, heart rate, and blood sugar, according to neurologist Phyllis Zee. She ran a clinical trial at Northwestern showing that \"Perhaps more than what you eat, when you eat relative to sleep may be as important,\" Zee said, <a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/wellness/2026/03/10/foods-for-better-sleep/\">according to the Washington Post</a>. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/13/when-you-stop-eating-may-matter-more-than-what-you-eat-for-better-sleep.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/13/when-you-stop-eating-may-matter-more-than-what-you-eat-for-better-sleep.html\">When you stop eating may matter more than what you eat for better sleep</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
      "date_published": "2026-03-13T18:25:33+00:00",
